9 An Act relating to health insurance; defining terms;
requiring coverage of certain anesthesia services;
10 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 7500 of Title 36, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. As used in this section:
18 1. “Anesthesia time” means the period beginning when an
19 anesthesia practitioner begins to prepare the patient for anesthesia
20 services in the operating room or an equivalent area and ends when
21 the anesthesia practitioner is no longer furnishing anesthesia
22 services to the patient. In counting anesthesia time for services
23 furnished, the anesthesia practitioner may include blocks of time
24 around an interruption in anesthesia time provided the anesthesia
